HEADWORD: Glynne
<hw>Glynne</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>A glen. See <er>Glen</er>. <note>[<mark>Obs.</mark>
singly, but occurring often in locative names in Ireland, as
<xex>Glen</xex> does in Scotland.]</note></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He could not beat out the Irish, yet he did shut them up within
those narrow corners and <qex>glyns</qex> under the mountain's foot.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

